<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10520839>
    dc:description "Fig. 9 Halimeda? sp. from Paleocene carbonates of the Chehel Kaman Formation, northeastern Iran. a, longitudinal oblique section. b, transverse section with medullar zone occupying about the half of the total diameter. c, tangential section showing cortical filaments. d, longitudinal section. e, oblique transverse section. f, specimen exhibiting a protuberance/swelling/ or branching. Thin-sections: NF 12-2 (a), NF 12-3 (b-c), Nf 12-4 (d, f), Nf 12-1 (e)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10520839/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

